gie Macnab, Design by Nature: Using Universal Forms and Principles in Design\n|\nCan we just stop pretending that skinny jeans are a good look on anyone? Can we just band together and go for a boot cut, please? Ladies?\n\n- Jennifer\n|\nYour presence is enough to go through life. More and more you observe life, more and more you can let lose yourself with the free flow of life.\n\n- Roshan\n|\nChrist the man died long ago, but Christ the idea of love, still exists, not in any church, rather in the mind of humans.\n\n- Abhijit\n|\nLook, don't just stare at the pages,' I used to tell my students. 'Become the characters. Live inside the book.\n\n- Wally Lamb, The Hour I First Believed\n|\nLet us emulate nature, let us bloom like a flower to fill the world with kindness, tolerance, tranquility, beauty and love.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhen we feel love and kindness toward others, it not only makes others feel loved and cared for, but it helps us also to develop inner happiness and peace.\n\n- Dalai\n|\nMore people would be depressed, if parents tried to please their children as frequently and as badly as children try to please their parents.\n\n- Mokokoma\n|\nFalling in love is more than infatuation. It is the need to feel whole, to feel safe, to be healed, to join together with someone, heart and soul.\n\n- Michael R. French, Why Men Fall Out of Love: What Every Woman Needs to Understand\n|\n..he had trampled her poor, pining heart, and the wound was still raw, even these many years later.\n\n- Ransom Riggs, Miss Peregrine’s Home for Peculiar Children\n|\nTim and Raine are coming in.''Are they insane?''Apparently.\n\n- Susan Bischoff, Heroes 'Til Curfew\n|\nTo be unpopular, you must look the part. Remember four words: plastic flowered swim cap.\n\n- Jennifer Ziegler, How Not to Be Popular\n|\nAnd on cold wintry nights she loves listening to Elvis croon 'Are you lonesome tonight?' just as I do.\n\n- Avijeet\n|\nTravel far enough, you meet yourself.\n\n- David Mitchell, Cloud 